heaviest_rainfall.status: The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm fell at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour over the 37.2 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The 4th ranked rain rate was recorded today with a peak rate of 16.2mm per hour, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  9.2mm of rain fell during the storm's 5.1 hours length.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: The record duration for continuous rain was set on 04 January 2025, the storm lasted 37.2 hours with a total precipitation of 36.8mm and it reached 4.6mm per hour at times.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 3.5°C), outside temperature (down 3.2°C), and inside temperature (down 2.0°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%) and rainfall (up 0.2 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 635 m), rainfall (down 0.2 mm), and light levels (up 4643 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1233 m), light levels (up 6608 lux), and rainfall (down 0.6 mm) when compared to today.
